comments: Robinson-Earl (OKC) jumps and turns while airborne and delivers contact to Washington's (CHA) side and affects his driving shot attempt.
Washington (CHA) brings his arm  forward and initiates contact to Joe's (OKC) neck area and affects his driving shot attempt.
Joe (OKC) reaches in and makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it away from Maledon (CHA) during the drive.
Joe (OKC) moves alongside Maledon's (CHA) path and marginal body contact occurs as they engage during the drive.
Joe (OKC) extends his arm to contest and makes clean contact with the ball during Maledon's (CHA) shot attempt near the rim.
Dort (OKC) moves forward in pursuit of the rebound and marginal body contact occurs with Maledon (OKC) as they engage.
Washington (CHA) touches the ball last before going out of bounds.
Washington (CHA) establishes himself and firms up over his left foot in Joe's (OKC) path and marginal body contact occurs as the pick is set.
Mykhailiuk (CHA) moves laterally alongside Giddey's (OKC) path and marginal body contact occurs as they engage during the driving shot attempt.
Dort (OKC) touches the ball last before going out of bounds.
Robinson-Earl (OKC) slightly brings his hands forward as he steps toward Washington (CHA) and marginal body contact occurs as they engage at the start of the drive.
Richards (CHA) extends his arms into Dort's (OKC) back and the contact dislodges him from his rebounding position, affecting his ability to pursue the loose ball.
Washington (CHA) extends his forearm into Williams' (OKC) body and initiates contact that affects his driving shot attempt.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court (defensive goaltending) was overturned to a legal block.
Joe (OKC) touches the ball last before going out of bounds.
Dort (OKC) reaches in and grabs Thor's (CHA) arm, initiating illegal contact that affects his SQBR.
Richards (CHA) jumps from point A to point B to deliver contact to Giddey's (OKC) body and affects his driving shot attempt.
Dort (OKC) reaches in and initiates contact with Mykhailiuk's (CHA) arm that affects his SQBR.
Dort (OKC) and Washington (CHA) mutually come together in pursuit of the loose ball and marginal body contact occurs.
